name: She's Out of Control
tagline: When an average-looking teenage girl gets a makeover, it's enough to turn make her father become overprotective of her.

name: Sunshine Cleaning
tagline: In order to raise the tuition to send her young son to private school, a mom starts an unusual business -- a biohazard removal/crime scene clean-up service -- with her unreliable sister.

name: The Pagemaster
tagline: A cowardly boy who buries himself in accident statistics enters a library to escape a storm only to be transformed into an animated illustration by the Pagemaster. He has to work through obstacles from classic books to return to real life.

name: The Last Stand
tagline: The leader of a drug cartel busts out of a courthouse and speeds to the Mexican border, where the only thing in his path is a sheriff and his inexperienced staff.

name: Chasing Amy
tagline: Holden and Banky are comic book artists. Everything's going good for them until they meet Alyssa, also a comic book artist. Holden falls for her, but his hopes are crushed when he finds out she's gay.

name: Lucky Lady
tagline: A trio of rum-runners during prohibition in the 1930s engage in a menage-a-trios after business hours.

name: Frankenstein
tagline: Horror classic in which an obsessed scientist assembles a living being from parts of exhumed corpses.

name: The Gift
tagline: A woman with extrasensory perception is asked to help find a young woman who has disappeared.

name: The King and I
tagline: Traveling to the exotic kingdom of Siam, English Schoolteacher Anna Leonowens soon discovers that her most difficult challenge is the stubborn, imperious King himself.

name: Sorority Row
tagline: A group of sorority sisters try to cover up the death of their house-sister after a prank gone wrong, only to be stalked by a serial killer.

name: The Protector
tagline: A young fighter named Kham must go to Australia to retrieve his stolen elephant. With the help of a Thai-born Australian detective, Kham must take on all comers, including a gang led by an evil woman and her two deadly bodyguards.

name: The Darjeeling Limited
tagline: A year after their father's funeral, three brothers travel across India by train in an attempt to bond with each other.

name: Sliding Doors
tagline: A London woman's love life and career both hinge, unknown to her, on whether or not she catches a train. We see it both ways, in parallel.

name: Big Night
tagline: A failing Italian restaurant run by two brothers gambles on one special night to try to save the business.

name: Glee: The 3D Concert Movie
tagline: A concert documentary shot during the Glee Live! In Concert! summer 2011 tour, featuring song performances and Glee fans' life stories and how the show influenced them.

name: Extraordinary Measures
tagline: A drama centered on the efforts of John and Aileen Crowley to find a researcher who might have a cure for their two children's rare genetic disorder.

name: Firewalker
tagline: A pair of adventurers try to track down an ancient Aztec/Mayan/Egyptian/Apache hoard of gold.

name: Breakin' All the Rules
tagline: Inspired by his fiancée (who dumped him), a man publishes a break-up handbook for men, becoming a bestselling author in the process.

name: Meet Dave
tagline: A crew of miniature aliens operate a spaceship that has a human form. While trying to save their planet, the aliens encounter a new problem, as their ship becomes smitten with an Earth woman.

name: Zelig
tagline: "Documentary" about a man who can look and act like whoever he's around, and meets various famous people.

name: Caddyshack II
tagline: When a crass new-money tycoon's membership application is turned down at a snooty country club, he retaliates by buying the club and turning it into a tacky amusement park.

name: Tales from the Hood
tagline: A strange funeral director tells four strange tales of horror with an African American focus to three drug dealers he traps in his place of business.

name: Strictly Ballroom
tagline: A maverick dancer risks his career by performing an unusual routine and sets out to succeed with a new partner.

name: End of the Spear
tagline: Two people come to the end of a spear in order to realize that the divisions between them are not real.

name: Sydney White
tagline: A modern retelling of Snow White set against students in their freshman year of college in the greek system.

name: Block Party
tagline: A mix of Dave Chappelle's sketch comedy and musical interludes, inspired in part by the 1973 documentary Wattstax.

name: Gone
tagline: A woman is convinced her kidnapper has returned when her sister goes missing.

name: Far from Home: The Adventures of Yellow Dog
The Adventures of Elmo in Grouchland
Girl with a Pearl Earring
tagline: A young peasant maid working in the house of painter Johannes Vermeer becomes his talented assistant and the model for one of his most famous works.

name: Knockaround Guys
tagline: The wannabe sons of mobsters go to a remote town in the Midwest, and get themselves into more trouble than anyone could anticipate.

name: Zoom
tagline: Former superhero Jack is called back to work to transform an unlikely group of ragtag kids into superheroes at a private Academy.

name: The Muse
tagline: A comedy about a neurotic screenwriter and his modern-day muse.

name: So I Married an Axe Murderer
tagline: A San Francisco poet who fears commitment has a girlfriend who he suspects may not be who she appears.

name: Graveyard Shift
tagline: In a very old textile mill, with a serious rat infestation, the workers discover a horrifying secret deep in the basement.

name: Wing Commander
tagline: Blair, a fighter pilot, joins an interstellar war to fight the evil Kilrathi who are trying to destroy the universe.

name: Police Academy 6: City Under Siege
tagline: Those bumbling cadets take to the streets when three inept goons successfully orchestrate a metropolitan crime wave.

name: The Legend of Drunken Master
tagline: A young martial artist is caught between respecting his pacifist father's wishes or stopping a group of disrespectful foreigners from stealing precious artifacts.

name: Pump Up the Volume
tagline: Mark runs a pirate radio station and causes an uproar when he speaks his mind and enthralls fellow teens.

name: The Conspirator
tagline: Mary Surratt is the lone female charged as a co-conspirator in the assassination trial of Abraham Lincoln. As the whole nation turns against her, she is forced to rely on her reluctant lawyer to uncover the truth and save her life.

name: Fair Game
tagline: Max Kirkpatrick is a cop who protects Kate McQuean, a civil law attorney, from a renegade KGB team out to terminate her.

name: Boys Don't Cry
tagline: Female born, Teena Brandon adopts his male identity of Brandon Teena and attempts to find himself and love in Nebraska.

name: Super Size Me
tagline: While examining the influence of the fast food industry, Morgan Spurlock personally explores the consequences on his health of a diet of solely McDonald's food for one month.

name: The Longshots
tagline: The true story of Jasmine Plummer who, at the age of eleven, became the first female to play in Pop Warner football tournament in its 56-year history.

name: Army of Darkness
tagline: A man is accidentally transported to 1300 A.D., where he must battle an army of the dead and retrieve the Necronomicon so he can return home.

name: Mulholland Falls
tagline: In 1950's Los Angeles, a special crime squad of the LAPD investigates the murder of a young woman.

name: Turbulence
tagline: After a shootout on a flight transporting prisoners, a stewardess must outwit a smooth-talking serial killer and land the plane herself.

name: The Beautician and the Beast
tagline: A New York cosmetologist mistakenly thought to be a science teacher is offered a job to teach the children of an Eastern European dictator.

name: Material Girls
tagline: Two wealthy sisters, both heiresses to their family's cosmetics fortune, are given a wake-up call when a scandal and ensuing investigation strip them of their wealth.

name: The Ref
tagline: A cat burglar is forced to take a bickering, dysfunctional family hostage on Christmas Eve.

name: The Words
tagline: A writer at the peak of his literary success discovers the steep price he must pay for stealing another man's work.

name: Das Boot
tagline: The claustrophobic world of a WWII German U-boat; boredom, filth, and sheer terror.

name: Something New
tagline: Kenya McQueen, an accountant finds love in the most unexpected place when she agrees to go on a blind date with Brian Kelly, a sexy and free-spirited landscaper.

name: The Powerpuff Girls
tagline: The movie shows the origin of the Powerpuff Girls before the cartoon series. It explains why they were born and why they dedicated their lives to fighting crime and the forces of evil.

name: The Shipping News
tagline: An emotionally-beaten man with his young daughter moves to his ancestral home in Newfoundland to reclaim his life.

name: Thumbelina
tagline: The tiny girl meets a fairy prince who saves her from the creatures of the woods.

name: Out of the Furnace
tagline: When Rodney Baze mysteriously disappears and law enforcement doesn't follow through fast enough, his older brother, Russell, takes matters into his own hands to find justice.

name: Extreme Prejudice
tagline: A Texas Ranger and a ruthless narcotics kingpin - they were childhood friends, now they are adversaries...

name: Casanova
tagline: Heath Ledger plays the fabled romantic as a man who, after failing to win the affection of a particular Venetian woman, strives to discover the real meaning of love.

name: Manhattan Murder Mystery
tagline: A middle-aged couple suspects foul play when their neighbor's wife suddenly drops dead.

name: The Lives of Others
tagline: In 1984 East Berlin, an agent of the secret police, conducting surveillance on a writer and his lover, finds himself becoming increasingly absorbed by their lives.

name: One Good Cop
tagline: One good cop has to fight the bad guys and take care of his partner's three little girls after he is killed in the line of fire.

name: Balto
tagline: An outcast half-wolf risks his life to prevent a deadly epidemic from ravaging Nome, Alaska.

name: CyberWorld
tagline: While our host hunts for destructive computer bugs, various shorts and clips of computer animation are featured.

name: Jane Eyre
tagline: A mousy governess who softens the heart of her employer soon discovers that he's hiding a terrible secret.

name: Chill Factor
tagline: A new biological chemical weapon that explodes up to temperatures over fifty degrees Fahrenheit, falls into the hands of two men who try to make sure that it doesn't get stolen by a terrorist.

name: Surviving Christmas
tagline: A lonely, obnoxious young millionaire pays a family to spend Christmas with him.

name: Be Kind Rewind
tagline: Two bumbling store clerks inadvertently erase the footage from all of the tapes in their video rental store. In order to keep the business running, they re-shoot every film in the store with their own camera, with a budget of zero dollars.

name: Deep Rising
tagline: A group of heavily armed hijackers board a luxury ocean liner in the South Pacific Ocean to loot it, only to do battle with a series of large-sized, tentacled, man-eating sea creatures who have taken over the ship first.

name: V.I. Warshawski
tagline: A female PI babysitting for a boyfriend gets stuck with his daughter and the case of her murdered father.

name: Big Trouble in Little China
tagline: An All-American trucker gets dragged into a centuries-old mystical battle in Chinatown.
